        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 1:39PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 138 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Cluster Springs, or near Turbeville, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
South Boston...
Redoak...
Clover...
Scottsburg...
Hitesburg...
Cluster Springs...
Virgilina...
and Staunton River State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
